a%20reasonable%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20it.%20You%20can%20calculate%20this%20by%20dividing%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-are-mortgage-closing-costs%5C%22%3Eclosing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20amount%20you're%20saving%20on%20your%20monthly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20paid%20%243%2C000%20to%20refinance%20and%20were%20able%20to%20lower%20your%20monthly%20payment%20by%20%24200%2C%20it%20would%20take%20you%2015%20months%20to%20break%20even%20on%20your%20refinance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Rate%20Trends%5C%22%3E5-Year%20Mortgage%20Rate%20Trends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%2030-year%20and%2015-year%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20trended%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FdBxcL%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Weekly%20mortgage%20rates%20over%20the%20last%205%20years%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20Factors%20Influence%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20Factors%20Influence%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-are-mortgage-rates-determined%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20determined%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20different%20factors%2C%20including%20larger%20economic%20trends%2C%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fstate-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Estate's%20current%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20type%20of%20loan%20you're%20getting%2C%20and%20your%20personal%20financial%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20of%20these%20factors%20are%20out%20of%20your%20control%2C%20you%20can%20work%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fhow-to-improve-credit-score%5C%22%3Eimproving%20your%20credit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20paying%20off%20debt%2C%20and%20saving%20for%20a%20larger%20down%20payment%20to%20ensure%20you%20get%20the%20best%20rate%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20Does%20the%20Fed%20Rate%20Affect%20Mortgage%20Rates%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20increased%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20dramatically%20in%202022%20and%202023%20to%20try%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control.%20Inflation%20has%20since%20slowed%20significantly%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20bit%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20policy%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20September%20meeting%2C%20the%20Fed%20started%20lowering%20rates%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20four%20years%2C%20and%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20expected%20to%20continue%20cutting%20at%20subsequent%20meetings.%20This%20should%20help%20mortgage%20rates%20ease%20in%202024%20and%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20spent%20the%20first%20half%20of%20this%20year%20relatively%20high%2C%20but%20they've%20been%20dropping%20for%20several%20months%20now%20and%20may%20go%20down%20further%20throughout%20the%20rest%20of%202024.%20They'll%20likely%20remain%20in%20the%20high%205%25%20range%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%20easing%20slowly%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20But%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20continue%20to%20ease%20throughout%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two%2C%20and%20it's%20possible%20rates%20could%20ultimately%20settle%20in%20closer%20to%205%25%20in%20a%20few%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Do%20Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Work%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Do%20Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20mortgage%20interest%20rate%20is%20how%20much%20you'll%20pay%20to%20borrow%20money%20for%20a%20home%20purchase%20or%20refinance.%20Each%20month%2C%20you'll%20make%20a%20payment%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20funds%20you%20borrowed%2C%20and%20a%20portion%20of%20that%20payment%20will%20go%20toward%20paying%20the%20interest%20you%20owe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20portion%20of%20your%20monthly%20payment%20that%20goes%20toward%20interest%20will%20go%20down%20over%20time%20through%20a%20process%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fmortgage-amortization-schedule%5C%22%3Eamortization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20you%20pay%20off%20more%20of%20your%20mortgage%2C%20the%20loan%20balance%20is%20reduced%2C%20lowering%20your%20interest%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20say%20you%20get%20a%20mortgage%20of%20%24300%2C000%20with%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%206.5%25%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%20Every%20month%2C%20you'll%20pay%20about%20%241%2C896.%20On%20your%20very%20first%20mortgage%20payment%2C%20only%20%24271%20of%20that%20amount%20will%20go%20toward%20reducing%20your%20loan%20balance%2C%20while%20%241%2C625%20will%20be%20paid%20in%20interest.%20But%20if%20you%20fast%20forward%2020%20years%2C%20%24992%20of%20that%20same%20monthly%20payment%20will%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20loan%20balance%2C%20and%20about%20%24905%20will%20go%20toward%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20ask%20your%20lender%20for%20an%20amortization%20schedule%20to%20see%20the%20breakdown%20of%20your%20payments%20throughout%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20or%20you%20can%20use%20an%20online%20amortization%20calculator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Often%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Change%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Often%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Change%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20change%20throughout%20the%20day%2C%20and%20they%20can%20fluctuate%20day-to-day%20or%20week-to-week%20based%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20the%20economy.%20If%20economic%20conditions%20are%20relatively%20stable%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20might%20not%20move%20much.%20But%20uncertainty%20or%20expectations%20that%20conditions%20will%20change%20soon%20can%20send%20rates%20up%20or%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20Shop%20for%20Mortgage%20Rates%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Shop%20for%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3EMortgage%20lenders%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20all%20offer%20the%20exact%20same%20rates%2C%20so%20you%20could%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20by%20shopping%20around%20for%20the%20best%20rate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20generally%20recommend%20getting%20quotes%20from%20a%20few%20different%20lenders%20%E2%80%94%20consider%20applying%20with%20at%20least%20three%20lenders%20to%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20range%20of%20rates%20available%20to%20you.%20If%20you're%20still%20early%20in%20the%20process%2C%20you%20can%20apply%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2