r%20his%20company%20was%20bought%20out%2C%20once%20after%20his%20job%20was%20shipped%20overseas%20(he%20trained%20his%20replacement)%2C%20and%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20after%20his%20team%20at%20a%20major%20cable%20company%20was%20downsized.%20%26quot%3BThree%20strikes%2C%20you're%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20somewhat%20painfully%20jokes.%20The%20company%20says%20age%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20it%20and%20that%20it%20was%20about%20title%2C%20but%20Sherman%2C%20who%20is%2067%2C%20notes%20that%20everyone%20who%20was%20cut%20from%20his%20team%20was%20over%2060.%20As%20he%20contemplates%20whether%20it's%20time%20to%20retire%2C%20the%20callousness%20with%20which%20his%20past%20employers%20treated%20him%20is%20making%20him%20rethink%20his%20give-it-all-on-the-job%20attitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20sort%20of%20raised%20that%20you%20do%20a%20hard%20day's%20work%20and%20you're%20honest%2C%20and%20things%20will%20work%20out%20for%20you%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20two-way%20street%20between%20you%20and%20your%20employer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20found%20out%20that's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etruly%20not%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherman%20and%20I%20talked%20after%20he%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20story%20I%20wrote%20about%20Gen%20Z%20taking%20more%20time%20off%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20HR%20platform%20Dayforce%20found%20a%2055%25%20increase%20in%20sick%20leave%20from%202019%20to%202023%2C%20with%20the%20biggest%20jump%20coming%20from%20the%20under-35%20crowd.%20Maybe%20the%20youngs%20have%20the%20right%20idea%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20and%20workers%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20take%20the%20time%20they%20have%20when%20they%20have%20it.%20Sherman%20built%20up%20360%20hours%20of%20sick%20leave%20at%20his%20last%20gig%20that%20went%20poof%20when%20he%20was%20let%20go%20%E2%80%94%20he%20wasn't%20credited%20or%20even%20paid%20out%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20have%20strong%20feelings%20about%20missing%20work.%20After%20publishing%20the%20article%20about%20Gen%20Z's%20predisposition%20to%20take%20time%20away%2C%20I%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20feedback%20from%20older%20generations.%20Some%20of%20it%20was%20predictable%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kids%20these%20days%26quot%3B%20complaints%20lamenting%20that%20nobody%20wants%20to%20work%20nowadays%2C%20that%20work%20ethic%20has%20disappeared%2C%20etc.%20But%20other%20comments%20struck%20a%20different%20note.%20People%20talked%20about%20respecting%20and%20even%20admiring%20Zoomers'%20willingness%20to%20lean%20out.%20Some%20even%20expressed%20regret%20at%20how%20much%20they'd%20given%20up%20in%20service%20of%20The%20Man%2C%20who%2C%20in%20retrospect%2C%20was%20in%20a%20one-sided%2C%20neglectful%20relationship%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20work%20culture%20hinges%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20ideal%20worker%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20who%20goes%20above%20and%20beyond%2C%20who's%20always%20available%2C%20whose%20life%20outside%20the%20office%20the%20higher-ups%20pay%20no%20mind%20to.%20It%20leads%20to%20some%20unhealthy%20behaviors%2C%20like%20presenteeism%2C%20where%20employees%20go%20to%20work%20even%20though%20they're%20not%20well%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20reason%20employees%20wind%20up%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-vacations-work-trends-culture-pto-travel-job-stress-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20vacation%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20a%20real%20one.%20It's%20not%20a%20great%20system%2C%20but%20it's%20one%20that%20workers%20have%20for%20decades%20bought%20into.%20It's%20also%20creating%20people%20who%20are%20left%20wondering%20later%20in%20their%20careers%20or%20in%20retirement%20if%20all%20that%20energy%20they%20put%20toward%20their%20jobs%20was%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wonder%20how%20many%20young%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20are%20hearing%20remorse%20from%20their%20boomer%20parents%20for%20having%20sacrificed%20their%20health%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Johnston%2C%20who%20retired%20from%20his%20job%20at%20a%20utilities%20company%20in%202020.%20He%20says%20he%20often%20warns%20his%20daughter%20and%20her%20cousins%20not%20to%20let%20work%20%26quot%3Bwreck%20their%20health.%26quot%3B%20Johnston%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20stakes%20%E2%80%94%20he%20got%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%20on%20his%20first%20day%20of%20retirement.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'You've%20got%20to%20be%20kidding%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20story%20you%20couldn't%20make%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20fine%20now%2C%20but%20looking%20back%20at%20his%20decades%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20he%20thinks%20about%20how%20much%20time%20he%20lost%20traveling%20for%20work%20or%20just%20going%20to%20and%20from%20the%20office.%20He%20spent%20two%20to%20three%20hours%20a%20day%20commuting%2C%20and%20over%2040%20years%2C%20that%20adds%20up.%20(That's%20why%20he%20thinks%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fremote-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20thing%20sounds%20good%2C%20too.)%20Johnston%20is%20Canadian%2C%20and%20he%20figures%20at%20least%20he%20didn't%20have%20it%20as%20bad%20as%20his%20American%20counterparts%2C%20who%20he%20said%20were%20great%20to%20collaborate%20with%20because%20they%20worked%20so%20hard%20but%20also%20had%20a%20work%20ethic%20that%20was%20%26quot%3Bnuts.%26quot%3B%20He's%20proud%20of%20what%20he%20accomplished%2C%20but%20he%20wishes%20he'd%20spent%20more%20time%20with%20his%20daughter.%20%26quot%3BMy%20father%20did%20the%20same%20thing%2C%20so%20for%20me%2C%20it%20wasn't%20that%20big%20of%20a%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20almost%20normal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDave%20Kotwitz%2C%20who%20worked%20for%20and%20then%20owned%20a%20Piggly%20Wiggly%20grocery%20store%20in%20Wisconsin%2C%20expressed%20a%20similar%20sentiment%20about%20missing%20out%20on%20watching%20his%20kids%20grow%20up.%20(I'll%20disclose%20here%20that%20I%20know%20Kotwitz%20%E2%80%94%20I%20went%20to%20school%20with%20his%20daughter%2C%20and%20his%20Pig%20was%20my%20Pig.)%20When%20he%20started%20out%20as%20a%20manager%2C%20he%20worked%20open%20to%20close%20for%20two%20years%2C%20and%20even%20after%20he%20became%20the%20owner%2C%20a%2040-hour%20workweek%20was%20a%20rarity.%20The%20time%20suck%20wasn't%20just%20the%20store%3B%20his%20involvement%20in%20the%20community%20%E2%80%94%20the%20local%20chamber%20of%20commerce%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%94%20ate%20up%20hours%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20evenings.%20His%20daughter%20brings%20up%20things%20that%20happened%20when%20she%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20and%20he%20doesn't%20have%20any%20recollection%20of%20them.%20He%20has%20no%20memory%20of%20her%20being%20on%20the%20golf%20team%20in%20high%20school%2C%20for%20example.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20pretty%20much%20buried%20in%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Kotwitz%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20got%20to%20be%20work-life%20balance%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20have%20work-life%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20retirement%2C%20Kotwitz%20has%20been%20doing%20more%20yardwork%20and%20taken%20up%20beekeeping%20and%20blacksmithing.%20He%20wishes%20he'd%20gotten%20into%20those%20a%20long%20time%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20they%20would%20have%20been%20more%20fun%20when%20he%20had%20more%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20I%20talked%20to%20for%20this%20story%20was%20so%20sold%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20relaxing%20on%20the%20job.%20There%20was%20Charlie%20Stuart%2C%20a%20documentary%20maker%20who%20retired%20in%202020%20and%20then%2C%20after%20realizing%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20play%20golf%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20decided%20to%20get%20his%20real-estate%20license.%20He'd%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20career%20working%20for%20himself%2C%20which%20is%20a%20blessing%20and%20a%20curse.%20You%20can%20make%20it%20to%20your%20kid's%202%20p.m.%20baseball%20game%2C%20but%20that's%20because%20you%20can%20go%20back%20to%20work%20at%2010%20at%20night.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20work%20for%20yourself%2C%20you're%20working%20for%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20jerks%20you've%20ever%20worked%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Vequist%2C%20a%20management%20professor%20in%20Texas%2C%20is%20happy%20with%20where%20he%20ended%20up%2C%20but%20he%20admires%20that%20his%20Gen%20Z%20students%20seem%20to%20prioritize%20their%20side%20gigs%20and%20passion%20projects%20over%20their%20day%20jobs.%20Paul%20Miola%2C%20who%20spent%20his%20career%20working%20in%20insurance%20and%20is%20now%20mostly%20retired%2C%20didn't%20need%20to%20wait%20to%20learn%20a%20lesson%20about%20the%20value%20of%20time%20off.%20Forty-five%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20took%20some%20days%20off%20to%20help%20his%20wife%20care%20for%20their%20first%20child%2C%20and%20when%20he%20returned%20to%20work%2C%20his%20manager%20told%20him%20it%20would%20affect%20his%20performance%20review.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shocked%20me.%20Like%2C%20really%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20the%20way%20things%20were%20then.%26quot%3B%20When%20Miola%20started%20managing%20people%2C%20he%20made%20sure%20to%20do%20things%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20will%20note%20here%20is%20that%20I%20talked%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20men%20for%20this%20story.%20While%20boomer%20women%20worked%20more%20than%20their%20own%20mothers%20did%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2019%2F02%2F14%2Fmillennial-life-how-young-adulthood-today-compares-with-prior-generations-2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20not%20employed%20at%20the%20same%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20millennials.%20In%20many%20boomer%20families%2C%20it%20was%20the%20expectation%20that%20the%20woman%20deal%20with%20childcare%20needs.%20If%20she%20was%20working%2C%20her%20boss%20may%20have%20been%20more%20understanding%2C%20too.%20The%20people%20I%20talked%20to%20were%20also%20generally%20more%20affluent%2C%20the%20types%20for%20whom%20the%20hard%20work%20had%20paid%20off.%20I%20wonder%20if%20there's%20more%20space%20for%20reflection%20there%20than%20there%20is%20for%2C%20say%2C%20single%20parents%20or%20blue-collar%20workers%20who%20feel%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20choice%20in%20their%20approach%20to%20work.%20They%20needed%20to%20put%20bread%20on%20the%20table%20and%20support%20their%20families%2C%20and%20that%20was%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Woods%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%20who%20founded%20Silvis%20Financial%2C%20based%20in%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20spends%20many%20of%20his%20days%20talking%20to%20pre-retirees%20thinking%20about%20their%20future%20and%20rethinking%20their%20past.%20No%20one%20ever%20tells%20him%20they%20wish%20they'd%20worked%20more%2C%20though%20many%20wish%20they'd%20invested%20more.%20Some%20say%20they%20wish%20they'd%20changed%20careers%20earlier%20on%20to%20improve%20their%20quality%20of%20life.%20Among%20younger%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20Gen%20X%20and%20below%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20sense%20that%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20repeat%20their%20parents'%20mistakes%2C%20workwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20had%20boomers%20as%20parents%2C%20then%20you%20grew%20up%20watching%20them%20work%20eight-plus%20hours%20a%20day%20five%20days%20a%20week%20for%2040%20years%2C%20and%20maybe%20they%20didn't%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20with%20their%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Woods%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20seen%20that%20and%20they%20want%20to%20do%20it%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewant%20to%20arrive%20at%20retirement%20with%20enough%20money%20in%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20there's%20more%20to%20the%20equation.%20They%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20capitalize%20on%20that%20time%2C%20whether%20by%20traveling%20or%20spending%20time%20with%20family%20or%20taking%20up%20hobbies%20or%20whatever%20else.%20They%20want%20to%20get%20there%20in%20good%20health%20so%20they%20can%20actually%20enjoy%20it%20all%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20guaranteed%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20work%20culture%20that%20has%20historically%20pushed%20people%20to%20run%20themselves%20ragged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidly%2C%20it's%20something%20I%20think%20about%20a%20lot.%20I%20have%20very%20much%20internalized%20the%20capitalist%20machine%20and%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20overwork.%20As%20much%20as%20I%20tell%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumerism-capitalism-optimization-culture-live-medium-average-good-enough-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit's%20fine%20to%20just%20be%20fine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20default%20setting%20at%20work%20is%20often%20sprinting.%20I%20cannot%20remember%20the%20last%20time%20I%20called%20out%20sick%2C%20even%20when%20I%20probably%20should%20have.%20And%20I%20worry%20that%20in%2030%20years%20I'll%20be%20set%20to%20retire%20and%20I'll%20wonder%20if%20everything%20I'm%20putting%20in%20now%20was%20worth%20it.%20That's%20assuming%20I'll%20get%20there%2C%20which%2C%20who%20knows.%20If%20Gen%20Z%20is%20easing%20off%20the%20gas%20pedal%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20maybe%20I%20should%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20boomers%20I%20talked%20to%20was%20in%20favor%20of%20people%20calling%20out%20of%20work%20willy-nilly.%20They%20pointed%20out%20that%20it's%20a%20strain%20on%20colleagues%20who%20are%20expected%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack%20and%20that%20it%20might%20ultimately%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20you.%20A%20couple%20also%20suggested%20that%20if%20a%20young%20worker%20is%20missing%20work%20so%20much%20%E2%80%94%20because%20of%20the%20stress%2C%20or%20maybe%20because%20they%20just%20hate%20it%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20probably%20time%20to%20look%20for%20a%20different%20job.%20If%20you're%20in%20your%2020s%20and%20you%20don't%20like%20the%20track%20you're%20on%2C%20it's%20a%20whole%20lot%20easier%20to%20jump%20to%20a%20different%20one%20now%20than%20in%20your%2050s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there's%20more%20to%20life%20than%20work%2C%20and%20if%20younger%20people%20are%20seeing%20that%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20great.%20It's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20being%2075%2C%20sitting%20on%20your%20porch%2C%20and%20wishing%20you'd%20put%20in%20more%20overtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-gen-z-sick-days-time-off-work-regret-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727257682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f33350d17aa3c7b2b5c615%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-gen-z-sick-days-time-off-work-regret-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Baby%20boomers%20are%20jealous%20of%20Gen%20Z's%20modern%20attitude%20toward%20calling%20out%20sick%20and%20taking%20time%20off%20of%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-gen-z-sick-days-time-off-work-regret-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20the%20Axis%20of%20Resistance%3F%20Can%20It%20Challenge%20Israel's%20Military%20Power%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20least%20558%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20across%20southern%20Lebanon%20following%20Israel's%20largest%20aerial%20offensive%20against%20Hezbollah%20since%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20Gaza%20war%20on%20October%207.%20The%20Lebanese%20health%20ministry%20reported%20that%20around%201%2C650%20have%20been%20wounded%2C%20with%20nearly%20100%20women%20and%20children%20among%20the%20dead.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Gaza%20faces%20a%20deepening%20humanitarian%20crisis%20as%20relentless%20Israeli%20airstrikes%20have%20killed%20over%2040%2C000%20Palestinians%20and%20displaced%20nearly%20the%20entire%20population.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20conflict%20lies%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-palestine-gaza-explained-axis-of-resistance-and-irans-proxy-network-across-middle-east-4534061%C2%A0%5C%22%3EAxis%20of%20Resistance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20informal%20alliance%20of%20state%20and%20non-state%20actors%20united%20against%20Western%20influence%20and%20Israeli%20aggression%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Axis%20of%20Resistance%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Axis%20of%20Resistance%20is%20a%20coalition%20led%20by%20Iran.%20It%20includes%20various%20militant%20groups%20and%20political%20organisations%20like%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%2C%20Syria's%20Assad%20regime%2C%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20Houthis%20in%20Yemen.%20These%20groups%2C%20backed%20by%20Iran's%20military%20expertise%20and%20financial%20resources%2C%20have%20intensified%20their%20opposition%20to%20Israeli%20actions%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20escalated%20after%20last%20October.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIran's%20primary%20tool%20in%20coordinating%20these%20forces%20is%20the%20Quds%20Force%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20(IRGC)%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20conducting%20covert%20operations%20and%20supporting%20militant%20groups%20across%20the%20region.%20Iran%20uses%20this%20network%20to%20solidify%20its%20influence%20and%20confront%20Israel%20and%20Western%20allies%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20multiple%20occasions%2C%20Yemen's%20Houthi%20movement%2C%20which%20has%20aligned%20itself%20with%20Iran%20and%20Hezbollah%2C%20have%20claimed%20responsibility%20for%20launching%20missiles%20and%20drones%20towards%20Israel.%20Yemen's%20Defence%20Minister%20Mohamed%20Nasser%20Al-Atifi%20recently%20declared%20that%20the%20Houthis%20were%20prepared%20to%20continue%20targeting%20Israeli%20forces%20after%20the%20Jewish%20state's%20attack%20on%20Lebanon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIran%20has%20methodically%20built%20this%20alliance%20over%20decades.%20It%20has%20long%20been%20accused%20of%20providing%20financial%20aid%20and%20military%20training%20to%20various%20factions%20within%20the%20Axis%2C%20especially%20Hezbollah%20and%20Hamas.%20According%20to%20US%20estimates%2C%20Iran%20provides%20around%20%24700%20million%20annually%20to%20Hezbollah%20and%20over%20%24100%20million%20to%20Palestinian%20groups%2C%20including%20Hamas%20and%20Islamic%20Jihad.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20the%20Axis%20of%20Resistance%20challenge%20Israel%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Axis%20of%20Resistance%20presents%20a%20significant%20military%20and%20ideological%20challenge%20to%20Israel.%20The%20country's%20military%20capabilities%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20advanced%20defence%20technology%20like%20the%20Iron%20Dome%2C%20give%20it%20a%20substantial%20advantage%20in%20terms%20of%20firepower%20and%20defence%20systems.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGroups%20like%20Hezbollah%20and%20Hamas%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20rely%20on%20asymmetric%20warfare%2C%20using%20rocket%20attacks%2C%20guerilla%20tactics%20and%20underground%20networks%20to%20combat%20Israel's%20superior%20conventional%20military%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20Lebanon%2C%20Hezbollah%20remains%20Israel's%20primary%20concern%20due%20to%20its%20proximity%20and%20large%20arsenal.%20A%20full-scale%20war%20between%20Hezbollah%20and%20Israel%20would%20likely%20be%20devastating%20for%20both%20sides%2C%20as%20Hezbollah's%20rockets%20could%20overwhelm%20Israeli%20defences%2C%20while%20Israeli%20airpower%20could%20inflict%20severe%20damage%20on%20Lebanon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20Gaza%2C%20Hamas%20continues%20its%20resistance%2C%20despite%20heavy%20Israeli%20bombardment.%20The%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20Gaza%20is%20deepening%2C%20with%20over%20thousand%20Palestinians%20reportedly%20killed%20and%20lakhs%20displaced%20since%20the%20conflict%20began.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727257500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F0dre2om4_lebanon-israel-attack_625x300_25_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-the-axis-of-resistance-can-it-challenge-israel-military-power-6645992%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%20558%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20across%20southern%20Lebanon%20following%20Israel's%20largest%20aerial%20offensive%20against%20Hezbollah%20since%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20Gaza%20war%20on%20October%207.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-the-axis-of-resistance-can-it-challenge-israel-military-power-6645992%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Why%20was%20he%20shot%20in%20head%3F'%3A%20Bombay%20HC's%