0they%20waited.%20Things%20got%20so%20crazy%20that%20one%20large-scale%20builder%20started%20accepting%20bids%20for%20homes%20on%20its%20website%2C%20sight%20unseen.%20%26quot%3BThat%20never%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20Keith%20Hughes%2C%20an%20Austin-based%20executive%20at%20the%20housing-research%20firm%20Zonda%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20that%20kind%20of%20frothy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20already%20moved%20out%20of%20Texas%20by%20that%20point%2C%20but%20I%20worried%20from%20afar%20that%20my%20hometown%20would%20meet%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20San%20Francisco%2C%20the%20poster%20child%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-inequality-housing-shortage-causes-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20shortage%20and%20all%20its%20associated%20woes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20feared%20that%20Austin%20would%20become%20known%20as%20a%20playground%20for%20the%20rich%2C%20a%20city%20where%20displacement%20and%20mind-boggling%20home%20prices%20marred%20the%20natural%20beauty%20that%20once%20made%20it%20such%20a%20draw.%20In%20my%20hand-wringing%2C%20though%2C%20I'd%20overlooked%20one%20crucial%20detail%3A%20Texas%20is%20better%20at%20building%20homes%20than%20almost%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustin-area%20builders%20immediately%20raced%20to%20meet%20the%20new%20demand%2C%20securing%20permits%20for%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FAUST448BP1FH%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%2C600%20new%20single-family%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%202021%20alone%2C%20a%2045%25%20jump%20from%20the%20same%20month%20in%202019.%20All%20told%2C%20plans%20for%20more%20than%20130%2C000%20new%20housing%20units%20of%20all%20kinds%20were%20approved%20from%202020%20through%202022.%20Once%20the%20paperwork%20goes%20through%2C%20it%20can%20take%20anywhere%20from%20a%20few%20months%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20for%20homes%20to%20hit%20the%20market%2C%20so%20for%