ip%20is%20key%20to%20the%20future%20of%20Asia.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20you%20can%20say%20that%20if%20the%20world%20is%20to%20be%20multi-polar%2C%20Asia%20has%20to%20be%20multi-polar.%20And%20therefore%20this%20relationship%20will%20influence%20not%20just%20the%20future%20of%20Asia%2C%20but%20in%20that%20way%2C%20perhaps%20the%20future%20of%20the%20world%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20according%20to%20news%20agency%20PTI.%20The%20event%20was%20hosted%20by%20Asia%20Society%20and%20Asia%20Society%20Policy%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EClosing%20the%20day%20with%20an%20engaging%20conversation%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdannyrrussel%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40dannyrrussel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAsiaPolicy%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40AsiaPolicy%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20on%20the%20theme%20%E2%80%98India%2C%20Asia%20%26amp%3B%20the%20World'.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAs%20rebalancing%2C%20multipolarity%20and%20plurilateralism%20become%20key%20words%20of%20Asian%20and%20global%20geopolitics%20and%20a%20changing%20world%20tries%20to%20adjust%20to%20the%20shocks%20of%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFcodPdlpA9%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FFcodPdlpA9%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Dr.%20S.%20Jaishankar%20(%40DrSJaishankar)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1838738414213971980%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2025%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20said%20India%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bdifficult%20history%26quot%3B%20with%20China.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20two%20countries%20who%20are%20neighbours%2C%20unique%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20they%20are%20the%20only%20two%20countries%20with%20over%20a%20billion%20people%2C%20both%20rising%20in%20the%20global%20order%20and%20who%20often%20have%20overlapping%20peripheries%2C%20including%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20have%20a%20common%20border.%20So%20it's%20really%20a%20very%20complicated%20issue.%20I%20think%2C%20if%20you%20look%20today%20in%20global%20politics%2C%20the%20parallel%20rises%20of%20India%20and%20China%20present%20a%20very%2C%20very%20unique%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20referred%20to%20a%20recent%20remark%20that%2075%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20disengagement%20problems%20with%20China%20have%20been%20sorted%20out.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20said%2075%20per%20cent%20of%20it%20has%20been%20sorted%20out%20-%20I%20was%20asked%20in%20a%20way%20to%20quantify%20-%20it's%20only%20of%20the%20disengagement.%20So%20that's%20one%20part%20of%20the%20problem.%20The%20main%20issue%20right%20now%20is%20the%20patrolling.%20You%20know%2C%20how%20do%20we%2C%20both%20of%20us%2C%20patrol%20up%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Jaishankar%20said%20patrolling%20arrangements%20have%20been%20disturbed%20after%202020.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we've%20been%20able%20to%20sort%20out%20much%20of%20the%20disengagement%2C%20the%20friction%20points%2C%20but%20some%20of%20the%20patrolling%20issues%20need%20to%20be%20resolved.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20once%20the%20disengagement%20issue%20is%20dealt%20with%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20the%20larger%20issue%20as%20both%20of%20us%20have%20brought%20a%20very%20large%20number%20of%20troops%20up%20to%20the%20border%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there%20is%20what%20we%20call%20the%20de-escalation%20issue%2C%20and%20then%20there%20is%20the%20larger%2C%20the%20next%20step%20is%20really%2C%20how%20do%20you%20deal%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20relationship%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bentire%203500%20kilometre-border%20between%20India%20and%20China%20is%20disputed%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you%20make%20sure%20the%20border%20is%20peaceful%20so%20that%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20relationship%20can%20move.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Jaishankar%20said%20several%20agreements%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20detailed%20how%20to%20ensure%20the%20border%20remained%20peaceful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20the%20problem%20was%20in%202020%2C%20despite%20these%20very%20explicit%20agreements%2C%20we%20saw%20that%20the%20Chinese%20-%20we%20were%20all%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Covid%20at%20that%20time%20-%20moved%20a%20large%20number%20of%20forces%20in%20violation%20of%20these%20agreements%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%20And%20we%20responded%20in%20kind%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20troops%20were%20deployed%20very%20close%20up%2C%20which%20is%20'very%20dangerous'%2C%20it%20was%20likely%20a%20mishap%20could%20happen%2C%20and%20it%20did%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%202020%20Galwan%20clash%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20there%20was%20a%20clash%2C%20and%20a%20number%20of%20troops%20died%20on%20either%20side%2C%20and%20that%20has%20since%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20overshadowed%20the%20relationship.%20So%20until%20we%20can%20restore%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20on%20the%20border%20and%20ensure%20the%20agreements%20signed%20up%20to%20are%20adhered%20to%2C%20it's%20obviously%20difficult%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20said%20the%20focus%20for%20the%20last%20four%20years%20had%20been%20to%20at%20least%20disengage%20the%20troops%2C%20meaning%20that%20they%20go%20back%20to%20the%20camp%2C%20the%20military%20bases%20from%20which%20they%20traditionally%20operate.%C2%A0%26quot%3BBecause%20right%20now%2C%20both%20sides%20have%20troops%20deployed%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727243400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F45o1tdjo_jaishankar_625x300_25_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A